<title>CANADA: Toronto Stock Exchange computer trading down.</title>
<headline>Toronto Stock Exchange computer trading down.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Toronto Stock Exchange said its computer trading system collapsed at 1054 EST/1554 GMT, coinciding with a huge volume of deals in Bre-X Minerals Ltd shares.</p>
<p>A total of 7.78 million Bre-X shares changed hands in the first 22 minutes of trading after the exchange reopened trading in the stock at 1030 EST/1530 GMT.</p>
<p>TSE officials were uncertain when the system would be in working order again.</p>
<p>On Thursday, the last day Bre-X traded, TSE systems went down twice during the session and forced the exchange to close 15 minutes early.</p>
<p>((Reuters Toronto Bureau (416) 941-8100))</p>
